*************************************************
*	How to Generate FUDforum Docs		*
*************************************************

Required Software:
	xsltproc (XSL & XML libraries)
	docbook xsl stylesheets
	pdftex (for generation of pdf file)


	

To generate the FUDforum 2 manual as a single HTML page you will need to do the following:
-----------

1) Edit manual.xsl and change the
	<xsl:import href="/usr/local/share/docbook-xsl/html/docbook.xsl"/>
   line to reflect the location of the html/docbook.xsl on your system

2) Run 
	xsltproc manual.xsl manual.xml 1> manual.html
	
3) If all works, you should have the complete manual inside manual.html




To generate a multi-page HTML manual you will need to do the following:
-----------

1) Edit manual_pages.xsl and change the
	<xsl:import href="/usr/local/share/docbook-xsl/html/chunk.xsl"/>
   line to reflect the location of the html/chunk.xsl on your system

2) Create html directory inside the current directory

3) Run
        xsltproc manual_pages.xsl manual.xml
        
4) If all works, you should have the manual's html pages inside the html directory, by accessing the index.html inside
   that directory you will be able to browse through the manual.
   
   
 
   
To generate a PDF manual do the following:
-----------

1) Edit manual_fo.xsl and change the
	<xsl:import href="/usr/local/share/docbook-xsl/fo/docbook.xsl"/>
   line to reflect the location of the fo/docbook.xsl on your system
   
2) Run 
	xsltproc manual_fo.xsl manual.xml > manual.fo   
	
3) Run
	pdflatex manual.fo

4) Run
        pdflatex manual.fo
   
   **note**
   	The second run is needed to generate the page numbers inside the TOC
 
5) If it worked, you should now have manual.pdf
